  <static seed="91" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring430.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{x^{2}+1.2x+0.35}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(x+0.5\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+0.7\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We look for factors of <m>0.35</m> that give <m>1.2</m> when added; the 
factors that work are <m>0.5</m> and <m>0.7</m> so</p>
<p><m>{x^{2}+1.2x+0.35}={\left(x+0.5\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+0.7\right)}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
